          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Components of a vector v are defined as follows             "
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "value": "       | ub[i] - x[i], if g[i] < 0 and ub[i] < np.inf\nv[i] = | x[i] - lb[i], if g[i] > 0 and lb[i] > -np.inf\n       | 1,           otherwise"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "According to this definition v[i] >= 0 for all i. It differs from the definition in paper  (eq. (2.2)), where the absolute value of v is used. Both definitions are equivalent down the line. Derivatives of v with respect to x take value 1, -1 or 0 depending on a case."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
